reviewText: While this isn't a great film, it is a funny movie, mainly due to Cheech Marin's immense likability and charisma. Emma Samms is good as the icy female lead whom Cheech charms into loosening up and Terence Cooper is in full Jason Robards-mode as her father. Some good gags, some not-so-good ones but it's not so bad that the director (Michael Gottlieb) needed to have the pseudonymous Alan Smithee take place of his own name. (3 stars)
summary: Shrimp on the Barbie a Fun Movie

reviewText: I was never a big fan of Cheech & Chong, but I love this movie. This is a movie about a Mexican American that is looking to make it big. This very rich girl is always trying to marry this men that her dad doesn't  approve of. She makes a bet with her dad that the next man she gets engaged to that he'll except. Well this is were Cheech comes in. He becomes a loud mouth and really is funny in this. Well worth watching.
